{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cd8d115e-547a-406b-ba69-8a11ba476cad","content":"Here's the workflow at `.github/workflows/publish.yml`. Key points:\n\n- **`id-token: write`** permission enables the OIDC token exchange — no API key needed.\n- Triggers on version tags (`v1.0.0`, etc.).\n- With trusted publishing, `dotnet nuget push` authenticates automatically via the OIDC token.\n\n**2. Configure NuGet.org (manual step):**\n\n1. Go to [nuget.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers](https://www.nuget.org/account/trusted-publishers)\n2. Add a new trusted publisher with:\n   - **Repository owner:** `myorg`\n   - **Repository name:** `mylib`\n   - **Workflow filename:** `publish.yml`\n   - **Environment:** *(leave blank unless you add a GitHub environment)*\n\n**3. To publish a release:**\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\nThe workflow will pack and push the package using the OIDC identity — no secrets or API keys stored in the repo.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d5f69e83-123b-4493-aa4d-e759ebc3d3ce","outputTokens":256,"requestId":"0406:1FD078:9DB214:B7D5F3:69F3FB0E"},"id":"adf1c853-5c33-4db2-b59b-14049cb0414e","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:00:06.426Z","parentId":"c8c72ea2-0f00-46fa-99e4-80250c6d4b0f"}
